class LUPrefix {
    int n;
    int longestPrefix;
    vector<bool> uploaded;
public:
    LUPrefix(int n) : n(n), longestPrefix(0) {
        uploaded.assign(n + 2, false);
    }

    void upload(int video) {
        uploaded[video] = true;
        while (longestPrefix + 1 <= n && uploaded[longestPrefix + 1]) {
            ++longestPrefix;
        }
    }

    int longest() {
        return longestPrefix;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) amortized per upload, O(1) per longest
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Maintain a boolean array to track which videos have been uploaded and a single integer `longestPrefix` that always equals the length of the longest contiguous prefix starting at 1. Each upload sets the corresponding flag and then increments `longestPrefix` while the next video is present. This guarantees O(1) amortized upload and O(1) query time with minimal memory overhead.

